data.title: Good food...cleanliness not so much
data.text: We came in for lunch to enjoy the beautiful weather on the lake. I really wanted to eat outside, but they have no shade for their outdoor dining, so indoors it was. The food was actually good (burger and chicken tenders), but no one was cleaning off the used/dirty tables. There were a bunch of guys standing around, but the tables were all full of dirty dishes. When someone would come in, they would take the dirty dishes off one table and move them to another. It was ridiculous.

data.title: Thanks for rescuing twin coves
data.text: My wife and I had met here 20+ years ago when it was Little Petes. We were a little disappointed  over the years as  the place changed hands but We think the new owner and theme has brought back the fun on this side of lake Grapevine. We also liked the improved menu which caters to the the traditional as well as the healthier patron.

data.title: Great Spot on the Lake!
data.text: I just found the "Rock'in S" lakeside restaurant and hot spot! Live music in the back with all the overhead doors open to the lake! Nice bar and restaurant in the front, with A/C cranking! The big burrito was tasty, but better yet, the salad was huge and well put together! 10 beers on tap, including "Lakefire"! This is just a super place to come up to on the weekend! I brought my kayak, and explored the inlets on the top of Grapevine lake! Much more woodsy, and rural than down on the Grapevine side! Great find!

data.title: Love Rockin S!
data.text: Great place to enjoy an atmosphere on the water. The fish tacos are awesome. Loaded with alvacados and you can choose corn tortillas if you are sensitive to gluten. I've also had the catfish and it was really good. Side salads are very fresh. My husband thought the fried shrimp plate was delicious. Great margaritas! This is a great place to relax and enjoy hanging out at the marina. Love Rockin S!

data.title: Good Appetizers
data.text:
wen there just for a couple of beers, they could do a lot better in the local beer selection area. They seem to have too many budwieser/miller options. 

The appetizers were really good, and the items on the menu, especially a couple of the burgers are going to get me to come back because the descriptions look amazing. 

Service was OK, but our guy seemed fairly new, so giving him the benefit of the doubt.
